The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Paris, April 2: Alcatel SA and Lucent Technologies Inc have agreed to merge. The two companies have announced this today. The deal will create a new Paris-based telecom equipment maker with sales of 21 billion euros ($25 billion) and generate 1.4 billion euros ($1.7 billion) of savings within three years. Alcatel said it agreed to buy Lucent to circumvent competition in the telecom equipment market.

 Calcutta, April 2: The Planning Commission has failed to file its approach paper for the Eleventh Five-Year Plan before the March 31 deadline. The paper is expected to be readied in the next two weeks. It may discuss the issues of capital account convertibility, besides labour reforms, agriculture and power.

 Beijing, April 2: Pan-American Aviation Holdings Ltd will invest up to $100 million to buy a 11-18 per cent stake in Grand China Airline, a subsidiary of the Hainan Airlines.

 New Delhi, April 2: The government wants to push up job creation by giving a special thrust to small and medium exporters, simplifying procedures and including new incentive schemes in the foreign trade policy, which will be announced on April 7.

 Mumbai, April 2: Reliance Communications Ventures Ltd today introduced a 10-year free incoming offer for its prepaid cell phone users. The Rs 795 single-recharge scheme comes with a preloaded talktime of Rs 25.




